{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7a781a4e-cf1e-4b91-82c7-5cf26efc04f1","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update NuGet packages:**\n   - Update `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it bundles Microsoft.Testing.Platform support).\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's no longer needed.\n   - Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` if you need coverage (optional).\n\n2. **Add an MSBuild property** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** the same way:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n- Each test project now produces a **standalone executable** (self-hosted).\n- Command-line options change from `--` (VSTest) to `--` with MTP-style switches (e.g., `--filter` stays, but `--logger` syntax differs).\n- If you use `dotnet test`, the property above ensures compatibility. You can also run the test exe directly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a0da9dcd-e5ed-4dcb-987d-dc17e258c0f2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to look at any code. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":345,"requestId":"7C13:D4E0A:262D6DF:2A34E6F:69F93E97"},"id":"f0c0005f-6d48-4805-8d85-bf9d2d0023e9","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:49:35.860Z","parentId":"d503fd41-1ad1-4d75-a36a-33bab546cd42"}
